    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>No, you don't \"inherit\" non-default constructors, you need to define the one taking a String in your class. Typically you use <code>super(message)</code> in your constructor to invoke your parent constructor. For example, like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class MyException extends Exception {\n    public MyException(String message) {\n        super(message);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
