      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "actually, that is incorrect.  If your code <b>uses</b> a constructor with one String argument, then you have to declare it.  However, an Exception subclass <b>can</b> be defined with no explicit constructors ... because Exception has a no-args constructor."
