    "creation_date" : 1353299103,
    "answer_id" : 13447668,
    "question_id" : 3776327,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Reason for this is explained in the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/IandI/subclasses.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><strong>Inheritance</strong></a> article of the Java Platform which says: </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>\"A subclass inherits all the members (fields, methods, and nested\n  classes) from its superclass. <strong>Constructors are not members</strong>, so they\n  are not inherited by subclasses, but the constructor of the superclass\n  can be invoked from the subclass.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
